#!/usr/bin/env -S uv run --script
# /// script
# requires-python = ">=3.11"
# dependencies = [
#     "httpx>=0.27",
# ]
# ///
"""
ical — personal Calendar.app CLI (JXA-backed; read + write, policy-gated).

No secret on disk. Auth is the one-time macOS Automation grant:
  System Settings → Privacy & Security → Automation → your terminal → Calendar

Writes are gated through the standard connections model — the same exit-4
write-gate every capability uses. A connection here carries policy, not a
credential: which Calendar.app calendars are in scope, and whether that
scope may be written. Selection: `--connection <id>` (anywhere on argv);
without the flag the registry's default applies (marked with * in the
`connections` output). Read verbs also respect the connection's scope —
when `calendars` is non-empty they read only those calendars.

Registry (first found wins, never merged):
  <project>/.capabilities/ical/connections.json
  ~/.config/ical/connections.json

Registry shape:
  {
    "default": "<id>",
    "connections": {
      "<id>": { "calendars": ["<Calendar.app name>", ...], "allow_write": <bool> }
    }
  }
  `calendars: []` (or omitted) means every calendar is in scope.
  `allow_write: false` (the safe default) blocks the write verbs.

Read commands:
  ical help
      Print this document.

  ical doctor
      Readiness — proves the macOS Automation grant by listing calendars.

  ical calendars [--json] [--connection ID]
      List calendars Calendar.app knows about (name, writable flag),
      restricted to the connection's scope when non-empty.

  ical events [--calendar NAME] [--from ISO] [--to ISO] [--limit N]
       [--json] [--connection ID]
      List events in a date window, sorted chronologically. Default window
      is today .. +7 days. Each event carries a stable id (uid), title,
      startDate, endDate, allDay flag, calendar name, and location.
      Datetimes are emitted as ISO 8601 with the local offset.

  ical show <event-id> [--json] [--connection ID]
      Show one event by uid: title, times, allDay, calendar, location,
      notes, url, and attendees (name + email). Only events on calendars
      in the connection's scope are visible.

  ical search <query> [--calendar NAME] [--from ISO] [--to ISO]
       [--field title|notes|any] [--limit N] [--json] [--connection ID]
      Search events. Default field 'any' matches title OR notes. Default
      window today .. +30 days.

  ical freebusy --from ISO --to ISO [--calendars NAME,NAME]
       [--include-noise] [--json] [--connection ID]
      Merged busy blocks across the given window. Restricted to the
      connection's scope (intersected with --calendars when given). By
      default excludes obvious noise (Birthdays / Holidays / Reminders /
      Siri Suggestions); --include-noise turns that off.

Write commands (gated: allow_write:true AND target calendar in scope,
else exit 4):
  ical create --calendar NAME --title T --from ISO --to ISO
       [--all-day] [--location L] [--notes N] [--url U]
       [--invitee EMAIL ...] [--alarm SPEC ...] [--connection ID]
      Create an event. --url is where a video-call link belongs.
      --invitee is repeatable (one email per flag). --alarm is repeatable;
      SPEC is either relative — `-15m`, `-1h`, `-30s`, `-1d` meaning that
      much before start — or an absolute ISO datetime. Prints the created
      event's uid.

  ical update <event-id>
       [--title T] [--from ISO] [--to ISO] [--all-day] [--no-all-day]
       [--location L] [--notes N] [--url U]
       [--add-invitee EMAIL ...] [--alarm SPEC ...] [--connection ID]
      Edit an existing event by uid; only provided fields change. Alarms
      passed replace the existing alarm set on the event.

  ical delete <event-id> [--connection ID]
      Delete an event by uid.

Calendar.app / JXA caveats — recorded honestly:
  • Whether attendee invitations are actually *sent* depends on the
    underlying account (iCloud/Exchange/CalDAV send; local calendars just
    record the attendee). ical adds the attendee via JXA and reports
    success at the JXA level, not the account level.
  • Alarms are created as `display alarm` entries. Absolute-ISO SPECs use
    `trigger date`; relative SPECs use `trigger interval` in seconds
    (negative = before start).
  • Event uids are Calendar.app's own — stable across a session.

<calendar> matches case-insensitively against a Calendar.app calendar's
name (trailing/leading whitespace ignored). Calendars are global to the
app — there is no <account> concept.

Contract commands (the same on every capability):
  ical stub                                 One-line awareness text.
  ical manifest --json                      Machine-readable declaration.
  ical connections                          Connection resolution report —
                                            each entry carries its calendars
                                            scope and allow_write flag; the
                                            default is marked with *. ical
                                            holds no credential, so every
                                            connection reports an empty key
                                            set.
  ical guide [<topic>]                      Guide topics / one guide body,
                                            fetched live from the docs base.
  ical ids list|get <l>|set <l> <v>|rm <l>  The project identifiers envelope
       [--note <text>]                      (.capabilities/ical/identifiers.json).
  ical refs                                 Menu of the project's reference
                                            files for this capability.

Exit codes:
  0  success
  2  auth — the macOS Automation grant is missing (doctor)
  3  not found (contract verbs)
  4  disabled by project policy, OR the active connection does not permit
     the write (allow_write:false, or target calendar outside scope).
     Ask the user; never lift the gate yourself.
  5  server / network (contract verbs)
  6  input / validation
  Domain commands print human-readable output and exit 1 on failure — the
  recorded deviation in this capability's deviations.md.
"""

import argparse
import json
import os
import subprocess
import sys
from datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone
from pathlib import Path
from typing import NoReturn


JXA_PRELUDE = r"""
ObjC.import('Foundation');

function env(name) {
  const v = $.NSProcessInfo.processInfo.environment.objectForKey(name);
  if (v.isNil()) return null;
  const s = ObjC.unwrap(v);
  return s === '' ? null : s;
}

function die(msg) { throw new Error(msg); }

function pad2(n) { return (n < 10 ? '0' : '') + n; }

function localISO(d) {
  if (!d) return null;
  try {
    const off = -d.getTimezoneOffset();          // minutes east of UTC
    const sign = off >= 0 ? '+' : '-';
    const ah = Math.floor(Math.abs(off) / 60);
    const am = Math.abs(off) % 60;
    return d.getFullYear() + '-' + pad2(d.getMonth() + 1) + '-' + pad2(d.getDate())
      + 'T' + pad2(d.getHours()) + ':' + pad2(d.getMinutes()) + ':' + pad2(d.getSeconds())
      + sign + pad2(ah) + ':' + pad2(am);
  } catch (e) { return null; }
}

function calendarsForNames(names) {
  const Cal = Application('Calendar');
  const all = Cal.calendars();
  if (!names || names.length === 0) return all;
  const wanted = names.map(n => (n || '').trim().toLowerCase());
  const out = [];
  for (const c of all) {
    const n = (c.name() || '').trim().toLowerCase();
    if (wanted.indexOf(n) >= 0) out.push(c);
  }
  if (out.length === 0) die('No calendar matches: ' + names.join(', '));
  return out;
}

function eventsInWindow(cal, fromDate, toDate) {
  try {
    return cal.events.whose({_and: [
      {startDate: {'>=': fromDate}},
      {startDate: {'<': toDate}}
    ]})();
  } catch (e) { return []; }
}

function eventSummary(e, calName) {
  let uid = null, summary = null, loc = null, allDay = false, start = null, end = null;
  try { uid = e.uid(); } catch (x) {}
  try { summary = e.summary(); } catch (x) {}
  try { loc = e.location(); } catch (x) {}
  try { allDay = e.alldayEvent(); } catch (x) {}
  try { start = localISO(e.startDate()); } catch (x) {}
  try { end = localISO(e.endDate()); } catch (x) {}
  return {
    id: uid,
    title: summary,
    startDate: start,
    endDate: end,
    allDay: allDay,
    calendar: calName,
    location: loc || null
  };
}

function eventFull(e, calName) {
  const base = eventSummary(e, calName);
  try { base.notes = e.description(); } catch (x) { base.notes = null; }
  try { base.url = e.url(); } catch (x) { base.url = null; }
  const atts = [];
  try {
    for (const a of e.attendees()) {
      let name = null, email = null;
      try { name = a.displayName(); } catch (x) {}
      try { email = a.email(); } catch (x) {}
      atts.push({name: name, email: email});
    }
  } catch (x) {}
  base.attendees = atts;
  return base;
}
"""


# --- Capability declaration (protocol 2) — one home for every contract fact --

NAME = "ical"
PROTOCOL = 2
SUMMARY = ("Calendar.app CLI over macOS Automation — read and write events "
           "across Calendar.app's configured calendars (calendars, events, "
           "show, search, freebusy, create, update, delete). Writes are "
           "gated by the connection's policy (scope + allow_write); auth is "
           "the one-time macOS Automation grant, no credential on disk.")
SCOPE = "user"      # credential scope: "project" | "user"
CRED_KEYS: list = []   # no credentials — auth is the one-time macOS Automation grant
WRITE_VERBS: list = ["create", "update", "delete"]  # gated per-connection
WRITE_DEFAULT = False   # safe default when a registry entry omits the flag
DOCS_BASE = ""      # upstream guides base URL; "" while no guides ship
TOPICS: list = []   # shipped guide topics
STATE = False       # True when the capability writes session/cache state
POST_INSTALL: list = []

_CONFIG_HOME = Path(os.environ.get("XDG_CONFIG_HOME") or (Path.home() / ".config"))
CREDENTIALS_ENV = _CONFIG_HOME / "ical" / "credentials.env"
_STATE_HOME = Path(os.environ.get("XDG_STATE_HOME") or (Path.home() / ".local" / "state"))


# >>> contract: capability core (generated — edit contract/preamble.py, run `capabilities sync-contract`) >>>

# --- Error reporting ---------------------------------------------------------

def _die(exit_code: int, code: str, message: str,
         hint: str | None = None, status: int | None = None) -> NoReturn:
    err: dict = {"code": code, "message": message}
    if hint:
        err["hint"] = hint
    if status is not None:
        err["status"] = status
    sys.stderr.write(json.dumps({"error": err}, ensure_ascii=False) + "\n")
    sys.exit(exit_code)


def _emit(value) -> None:
    if isinstance(value, str):
        sys.stdout.write(value)
        if value and not value.endswith("\n"):
            sys.stdout.write("\n")
    else:
        sys.stdout.write(json.dumps(value, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2) + "\n")


# --- Project / file plumbing -------------------------------------------------

def _parse_env_file(path: Path) -> dict:
    """Parse a KEY=VALUE env/dotenv file. Missing/unreadable file -> {}."""
    out: dict = {}
    try:
        text = path.read_text()
    except OSError:
        return out
    for line in text.splitlines():
        line = line.strip()
        if not line or line.startswith("#") or "=" not in line:
            continue
        k, v = line.split("=", 1)
        k = k.strip()
        if k.startswith("export "):
            k = k[len("export "):].strip()
        out[k] = v.strip().strip('"').strip("'")
    return out


def _project_root() -> Path | None:
    """Nearest project root, walking up from $CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR (else cwd):
    the first directory holding .capabilities/, .env(.local), or .git.
    $HOME is never a project root (the machine registry lives there)."""
    start = os.environ.get("CLAUDE_PROJECT_DIR") or os.getcwd()
    here = Path(start).resolve()
    home = Path.home().resolve()
    for d in (here, *here.parents):
        if d == home:
            return None
        if ((d / ".capabilities").is_dir() or (d / ".env").exists()
                or (d / ".env.local").exists() or (d / ".git").is_dir()):
            return d
    return None


def _project_env() -> dict:
    """Project .env(.local) at the project root. .env.local overrides .env."""
    root = _project_root()
    if root is None:
        return {}
    merged = _parse_env_file(root / ".env")
    merged.update(_parse_env_file(root / ".env.local"))  # .local wins
    return merged


def _gate() -> None:
    """absent → run; enabled → run; disabled → exit 4. Unreadable never blocks."""
    root = _project_root()
    if root is None:
        return
    gate_file = root / ".capabilities" / "settings.json"
    try:
        entry = json.loads(gate_file.read_text()).get("capabilities", {}).get(NAME)
    except (OSError, ValueError):
        return
    if isinstance(entry, dict) and entry.get("enabled") is False:
        _die(4, "disabled",
             f"{NAME} is disabled in this project ({gate_file})",
             "Do not enable it yourself — ask the user whether to enable it, then stop.")


def _env_dir() -> Path | None:
    """The capability's envelope dir in the project: .capabilities/<NAME>/."""
    root = _project_root()
    return (root / ".capabilities" / NAME) if root is not None else None


def _state_dir() -> Path:
    """State follows the scope of the credentials that minted it; project state
    lands inside the envelope only where .capabilities/ already exists."""
    if SCOPE == "project":
        root = _project_root()
        if root is not None and (root / ".capabilities").is_dir():
            return root / ".capabilities" / NAME / "state"
    return _STATE_HOME / NAME


# --- Capability contract (protocol 2) — the declaration surface --------------

def _docs_base() -> str:
    key = f"{NAME.upper()}_DOCS_BASE"
    return (_project_env().get(key)
            or _parse_env_file(CREDENTIALS_ENV).get(key)
            or os.environ.get(key)
            or DOCS_BASE)


def _cmd_guide(argv: list[str]) -> None:
    if not argv:
        _emit(sorted(TOPICS)); return
    topic = argv[0]
    if topic not in TOPICS:
        _die(3, "not_found", f"no guide topic {topic!r}",
             f"topics: {', '.join(sorted(TOPICS)) or 'none shipped'}")
    import httpx as _hx
    url = _docs_base().rstrip("/") + "/" + topic + ".md"
    cache_dir = _STATE_HOME / NAME / "guides"
    cache, etag_f = cache_dir / f"{topic}.md", cache_dir / f"{topic}.etag"
    headers = {}
    if cache.exists() and etag_f.exists():
        headers["If-None-Match"] = etag_f.read_text().strip()
    try:
        resp = _hx.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=10.0, follow_redirects=True)
        if resp.status_code == 200:
            cache_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
            cache.write_text(resp.text)
            if resp.headers.get("etag"):
                etag_f.write_text(resp.headers["etag"])
            _emit(resp.text); return
        if resp.status_code == 304 and cache.exists():
            _emit(cache.read_text()); return
        if resp.status_code == 404:
            _die(3, "not_found", f"guide {topic!r} missing upstream", url)
        raise _hx.HTTPError(f"upstream returned {resp.status_code}")
    except _hx.HTTPError as e:
        if cache.exists():
            sys.stderr.write(json.dumps(
                {"warning": f"upstream unreachable; serving cached copy ({e})"},
                ensure_ascii=False) + "\n")
            _emit(cache.read_text()); return
        _die(5, "network_error", f"could not fetch guide {topic!r}; no cache exists", url)


def _render_ids_markdown(data: dict) -> str:
    """Render the {label: {value, note}} envelope as the labelled markdown
    list the manager's `capabilities ids <NAME>` also produces — one shared
    format across the ids surface and the identifiers section of `help`."""
    lines: list[str] = []
    for label, entry in sorted(data.items()):
        entry = entry if isinstance(entry, dict) else {"value": entry}
        v = entry.get("value")
        vs = f"`{v}`" if isinstance(v, str) else "`" + json.dumps(v, ensure_ascii=False) + "`"
        line = f"- **{label}**: {vs}"
        note = entry.get("note")
        if note:
            line += f" — {note}"
        lines.append(line)
    return "\n".join(lines)


def _identifiers_section() -> str:
    """The Identifiers block appended to the bare top-level help — deterministic
    first-touch surfacing of `.capabilities/<NAME>/identifiers.json` so an
    agent following the `<NAME> help` startup protocol loads the discovered
    labels/values/notes into context at once. Empty when no project envelope
    or nothing recorded (do not bloat help with an empty section)."""
    envdir = _env_dir()
    if envdir is None:
        return ""
    ids_file = envdir / "identifiers.json"
    if not ids_file.exists():
        return ""
    try:
        data = json.loads(ids_file.read_text())
    except (OSError, ValueError):
        return ""
    if not isinstance(data, dict) or not data:
        return ""
    header = (
        "\n═══ Identifiers ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n"
        f"Structural lookups discovered for `{NAME}` in this project. Fetch a single\n"
        f"raw value with `{NAME} ids get <label>`; the full envelope is also at\n"
        f"`capabilities ids {NAME}`.\n\n"
    )
    return header + _render_ids_markdown(data) + "\n"


def _cmd_help() -> None:
    """Bare top-level help: the CLI's HELP body (module-level `HELP` if
    defined, else the module docstring), then the project's Identifiers
    section. Only fires when no extra args follow — per-verb help stays
    untouched so `<NAME> help <subcommand>` is not intercepted."""
    g = globals()
    text = g.get("HELP") or g.get("__doc__") or ""
    if text.startswith("\n"):
        text = text.lstrip("\n")
    sys.stdout.write(text)
    if text and not text.endswith("\n"):
        sys.stdout.write("\n")
    section = _identifiers_section()
    if section:
        sys.stdout.write(section)


def _cmd_ids(argv: list[str]) -> None:
    sub = argv[0] if argv else "list"
    envdir = _env_dir()
    ids_file = (envdir / "identifiers.json") if envdir else None
    data: dict = {}
    if ids_file and ids_file.exists():
        try:
            data = json.loads(ids_file.read_text())
        except ValueError:
            _die(6, "bad_envelope", f"{ids_file} is not valid JSON")
    if sub == "list":
        _emit(data); return
    if sub == "get":
        if len(argv) < 2 or argv[1] not in data:
            _die(3, "not_found", "unknown identifier label",
                 f"`{NAME} ids list` shows the labels")
        _emit((data[argv[1]] or {}).get("value")); return
    if sub == "set":
        if len(argv) < 3:
            _die(6, "input", f"usage: {NAME} ids set <label> <value> [--note <text>]")
        if envdir is None or not envdir.parent.is_dir():
            _die(6, "no_envelope", "no .capabilities/ envelope in this project",
                 "run `capabilities init` first")
        label, raw = argv[1], argv[2]
        try:
            value = json.loads(raw)
        except ValueError:
            value = raw
        note = ""
        if "--note" in argv:
            ni = argv.index("--note")
            if ni + 1 >= len(argv):
                _die(6, "input", "--note needs a value")
            note = argv[ni + 1]
        data[label] = {"value": value, "note": note or (data.get(label) or {}).get("note", "")}
        envdir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
        ids_file.write_text(json.dumps(data, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2, sort_keys=True) + "\n")
        _emit({"set": label}); return
    if sub == "rm":
        if len(argv) < 2 or argv[1] not in data:
            _die(3, "not_found", "unknown identifier label",
                 f"`{NAME} ids list` shows the labels")
        del data[argv[1]]
        ids_file.write_text(json.dumps(data, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2, sort_keys=True) + "\n")
        _emit({"removed": argv[1]}); return
    _die(6, "input", f"unknown ids subcommand {sub!r}", f"{NAME} ids list|get|set|rm")


def _cmd_refs() -> None:
    envdir = _env_dir()
    refdir = (envdir / "reference") if envdir else None
    out = []
    if refdir and refdir.is_dir():
        for md in sorted(refdir.glob("*.md")):
            name = desc = None
            try:
                lines = md.read_text().splitlines()
            except OSError:
                continue
            if lines and lines[0].strip() == "---":
                for line in lines[1:30]:
                    if line.strip() == "---":
                        break
                    if line.startswith("name:"):
                        name = line.split(":", 1)[1].strip()
                    elif line.startswith("description:"):
                        desc = line.split(":", 1)[1].strip()
            if name:
                out.append({"name": name, "description": desc or "", "path": str(md)})
    _emit(out)


def _contract(argv: list[str]) -> None:
    """Dispatch the contract verbs; domain verbs fall through to the CLI's own
    parser. Runs after _gate(), before any credential is resolved.

    `help` is a contract verb only when bare (no extra args) — the top-level
    dump plus the Identifiers section. `<NAME> help <subcommand>` falls
    through to the CLI so per-verb help stays clean."""
    cmd = argv[0] if argv else ""
    if cmd == "stub":
        _emit(f"{SUMMARY} Run `{NAME} help`.")
    elif cmd == "manifest":
        _emit({"name": NAME, "protocol": PROTOCOL, "summary": SUMMARY,
               "credentials": {"scope": SCOPE, "keys": CRED_KEYS},
               "docs": {"base": DOCS_BASE, "topics": sorted(TOPICS)},
               "state": STATE, "post_install": POST_INSTALL})
    elif cmd == "guide":
        _cmd_guide(argv[1:])
    elif cmd == "ids":
        _cmd_ids(argv[1:])
    elif cmd == "refs":
        _cmd_refs()
    elif cmd == "connections":
        _cmd_connections()
    elif cmd == "help" and len(argv) == 1:
        _cmd_help()
    else:
        return
    sys.exit(0)

# <<< contract: capability core <<<


# >>> contract: connections (generated — edit contract/preamble.py, run `capabilities sync-contract`) >>>

def _resolve_env_key(key: str) -> tuple[str | None, str | None, Path | None]:
    """Resolve one env key through cascade tiers 2-4: project .env(.local) →
    user credentials.env → process env. Returns (value, tier, source)."""
    root = _project_root()
    if root is not None:
        for fname in (".env.local", ".env"):
            val = _parse_env_file(root / fname).get(key)
            if val:
                return val, "project", root / fname
    val = _parse_env_file(CREDENTIALS_ENV).get(key)
    if val:
        return val, "user", CREDENTIALS_ENV
    val = os.environ.get(key)
    if val:
        return val, "env", None
    return None, None, None


def _mask(value: str) -> str:
    return ("…" + value[-4:]) if len(value) >= 8 else "****"


def _connections_registry() -> tuple[dict | None, Path | None]:
    """The connections envelope and its path: project envelope first, else the
    user config home. First found wins, never merged; (None, None) when neither
    declares one (the implicit default connection applies)."""
    envdir = _env_dir()
    candidates = ([envdir / "connections.json"] if envdir else []) + \
                 [_CONFIG_HOME / NAME / "connections.json"]
    for reg_file in candidates:
        if not reg_file.is_file():
            continue
        try:
            raw = json.loads(reg_file.read_text())
        except (ValueError, OSError) as e:
            _die(6, "bad_config", f"cannot read {reg_file}: {e}")
        if not isinstance(raw, dict) or not isinstance(raw.get("connections"), dict) \
                or not raw["connections"]:
            _die(6, "bad_config", f"{reg_file} is not a connections envelope",
                 'expected {"default": "<id>", "connections": { ... }}')
        return raw, reg_file
    return None, None


def _select_connection(reg: dict | None, wanted: str | None) -> tuple[str, dict | None]:
    """flag → default pointer → sole entry → die 6. No registry → the implicit
    default. A connection's own `address` field selects it too (used where a
    connection carries a human-recognizable address; absent fields never match)."""
    if reg is None:
        if wanted and wanted != "default":
            _die(6, "unknown_connection",
                 "no connections registry; the sole connection is 'default'",
                 "the implicit default resolves from the credential cascade")
        return "default", None
    conns = reg["connections"]
    if wanted:
        if wanted in conns:
            return wanted, conns[wanted]
        for cid, entry in conns.items():
            if (entry or {}).get("address", "").lower() == wanted.lower():
                return cid, entry
        _die(6, "unknown_connection", f"no connection matches {wanted!r}",
             f"known: {', '.join(conns)}")
    default = reg.get("default")
    if default:
        if default not in conns:
            _die(6, "bad_default", f"default points to unknown connection {default!r}",
                 f"known: {', '.join(conns)}")
        return default, conns[default]
    if len(conns) == 1:
        cid = next(iter(conns))
        return cid, conns[cid]
    _die(6, "ambiguous_connection",
         f"registry defines {len(conns)} connections and no default; "
         f"pass --connection <id>",
         f"known: {', '.join(conns)}")


def _write_gate(conn_id: str, allow_write: bool, verb: str) -> None:
    """Policy from the committed registry; nothing in the cascade lifts it."""
    if verb in WRITE_VERBS and not allow_write:
        _die(4, "read_only",
             f"connection {conn_id!r} does not allow writes",
             "Do not lift the gate yourself — ask the user; granting is "
             "`allow_write: true` on this connection in connections.json.")


def _key_report(key: str, secret: bool, required: bool,
                value: str | None, tier: str | None, source) -> dict:
    return {"key": key, "secret": secret, "required": required,
            "set": bool(value), "tier": tier if value else None,
            "source": str(source) if (value and source) else None,
            "value": (_mask(value) if secret else value) if value else None}


def _missing_required(keys: list) -> list:
    """Required report rows (from _key_report) that did not resolve through the
    cascade — empty ⇒ credentials present. The primitive behind doctor's
    network-free readiness gate, read from the same per-key resolution
    `connections` reports, so the gate and the report can never disagree."""
    return [k["key"] for k in keys if k["required"] and not k["set"]]


def _doctor_gate(report: dict, wanted: str | None) -> None:
    """doctor's network-free readiness gate. Refuse with exit 2 — naming the
    unresolved required keys, before any round-trip — when a connection under
    test cannot resolve its required config through the cascade, so readiness is
    judged by the same resolution `connections` reports, never a parallel check.
    Checks the selected connection, else every connection in the report."""
    conns = report.get("connections") or {}
    targets = [wanted] if (wanted and wanted in conns) else list(conns)
    problems: dict = {}
    for cid in targets:
        miss = _missing_required((conns.get(cid) or {}).get("keys") or [])
        if miss:
            problems[cid] = miss
    if problems:
        detail = "; ".join(f"{c}: {', '.join(ks)}" for c, ks in sorted(problems.items()))
        _die(2, "credentials_missing",
             f"unresolved required config — {detail}",
             f"set each in the project .env/.env.local, the user credentials.env, "
             f"or process env; `{NAME} connections` shows where every value resolves")

# <<< contract: connections <<<


# --- Connections (capability-specific) --------------------------------------

def _conn_scope(entry: dict | None) -> list[str]:
    """The calendars in scope for one connection. Empty ⇒ every calendar."""
    if not isinstance(entry, dict):
        return []
    raw = entry.get("calendars") or []
    return [str(x).strip() for x in raw if str(x).strip()]


def _scope_permits(scope: list[str], calendar_name: str) -> bool:
    """Scope empty ⇒ every calendar. Otherwise case-insensitive match."""
    if not scope:
        return True
    n = (calendar_name or "").strip().lower()
    return any(s.strip().lower() == n for s in scope)


def _connections_report() -> dict:
    """The resolution report. ical holds no credential and reaches no remote
    service — auth is the one-time macOS Automation grant — so a registry, if
    present, only names connections; each carries policy (calendars scope +
    allow_write) and reports an empty key set (CRED_KEYS is empty). The default
    entry is marked with * in `default_marker`. With no registry the sole
    connection is the implicit `default`. Local only: no network, no
    Calendar.app call."""
    reg, reg_path = _connections_registry()
    report: dict = {"default": None, "connections": {}}
    if reg is None:
        keys = [_key_report(k["key"], k["secret"], k["required"],
                            *_resolve_env_key(k["key"])) for k in CRED_KEYS]
        report["default"] = "default*"
        report["connections"]["default"] = {
            "calendars": [], "allow_write": WRITE_DEFAULT, "keys": keys}
        return report
    conns = reg["connections"]
    default_id = reg.get("default") or \
        (next(iter(conns)) if len(conns) == 1 else None)
    report["default"] = (default_id + "*") if default_id else None
    for cid, entry in conns.items():
        entry = entry if isinstance(entry, dict) else {}
        keys = [_key_report(k["key"], k["secret"], k["required"],
                            *_resolve_env_key(k["key"])) for k in CRED_KEYS]
        report["connections"][cid] = {
            "calendars": _conn_scope(entry),
            "allow_write": bool(entry.get("allow_write", WRITE_DEFAULT)),
            "keys": keys}
    return report


def _cmd_connections() -> None:
    _emit(_connections_report())


# --- Active connection (selected by --connection or the registry default) ---

def _active_conn(wanted: str | None) -> tuple[str, list[str], bool]:
    """Resolve the active connection: (id, calendars_scope, allow_write)."""
    reg, _ = _connections_registry()
    cid, entry = _select_connection(reg, wanted)
    if entry is None:  # implicit default (no registry)
        return cid, [], WRITE_DEFAULT
    return (cid, _conn_scope(entry),
            bool(entry.get("allow_write", WRITE_DEFAULT)))


def _enforce_write(cid: str, scope: list[str], allow_write: bool,
                   verb: str, calendar_name: str) -> None:
    """The standard exit-4 write-gate, extended: also fail when the target
    calendar is outside the connection's calendars scope."""
    _write_gate(cid, allow_write, verb)   # exits 4 on allow_write:false
    if not _scope_permits(scope, calendar_name):
        _die(4, "out_of_scope",
             f"connection {cid!r} does not include calendar {calendar_name!r}",
             "Do not lift the gate yourself — ask the user; scope lives in "
             "the `calendars` list on this connection in connections.json.")


def _extract_connection(argv: list[str]) -> tuple[list[str], str | None]:
    """Pull --connection <id> (or --connection=<id>) out of argv so it works in
    any position. Returns (cleaned_argv, connection_id_or_None)."""
    wanted = None
    cleaned: list[str] = []
    i = 0
    while i < len(argv):
        a = argv[i]
        if a == "--connection" and i + 1 < len(argv):
            wanted = argv[i + 1]; i += 2; continue
        if a.startswith("--connection="):
            wanted = a.split("=", 1)[1]; i += 1; continue
        cleaned.append(a); i += 1
    return cleaned, wanted


# --- JXA runner -------------------------------------------------------------

def run_jxa(script_body: str, env_extras: dict | None = None, timeout: int = 600):
    """Execute a JXA script via osascript; return parsed JSON or None."""
    full_script = JXA_PRELUDE + "\n" + script_body
    env = os.environ.copy()
    if env_extras:
        for k, v in env_extras.items():
            env[k] = "" if v is None else str(v)
    try:
        result = subprocess.run(
            ["osascript", "-l", "JavaScript", "-e", full_script],
            capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=timeout, env=env,
        )
    except FileNotFoundError:
        sys.exit("osascript not found — this CLI only works on macOS.")
    if result.returncode != 0:
        err = result.stderr.strip()
        if "-1743" in err or "Not authorized to send Apple events" in err:
            sys.exit(
                "Calendar.app automation is not authorized for this terminal.\n"
                "  Grant: System Settings → Privacy & Security → Automation\n"
                "         → [your terminal app] → enable Calendar\n"
                "  Then run the command again.\n"
                f"  ({err})"
            )
        sys.exit(f"osascript failed: {err}")
    out = result.stdout.strip()
    if not out:
        return None
    try:
        return json.loads(out)
    except json.JSONDecodeError:
        return out


# --- Date helpers -----------------------------------------------------------

def _local_now() -> datetime:
    return datetime.now().astimezone()


def _parse_iso(s: str, fallback: datetime) -> datetime:
    if not s:
        return fallback
    try:
        # datetime.fromisoformat handles offsets on 3.11+.
        return datetime.fromisoformat(s)
    except ValueError:
        sys.exit(f"bad ISO datetime: {s!r}")


def _iso(d: datetime) -> str:
    if d.tzinfo is None:
        d = d.astimezone()
    return d.isoformat(timespec="seconds")


def _default_window(from_s: str | None, to_s: str | None,
                    days_default: int) -> tuple[datetime, datetime]:
    now = _local_now()
    # Anchor "today" at local midnight so the window is agent-friendly.
    today = now.replace(hour=0, minute=0, second=0, microsecond=0)
    frm = _parse_iso(from_s, today)
    to = _parse_iso(to_s, today + timedelta(days=days_default))
    if to <= frm:
        sys.exit("--to must be after --from")
    return frm, to


# --- Scope helpers (read verbs) ---------------------------------------------

def _resolve_read_calendars(args) -> list[str]:
    """Effective calendar filter for a read verb: user's --calendar intersected
    with the connection scope. `[]` means 'every calendar' (JXA default).
    Explicit --calendar outside scope fails exit 4 so the agent sees the wall,
    the same signal the write gate raises."""
    scope = getattr(args, "_scope", [])
    calendar = getattr(args, "calendar", None)
    if calendar:
        if scope and not _scope_permits(scope, calendar):
            _die(4, "out_of_scope",
                 f"connection {args._conn_id!r} does not include calendar "
                 f"{calendar!r}",
                 "Do not lift the gate yourself — ask the user to widen the "
                 "connection's `calendars` scope in connections.json.")
        return [calendar]
    return list(scope)


# --- Domain commands --------------------------------------------------------

def cmd_doctor():
    """Cheapest authenticated round-trip: the Automation grant + calendar list."""
    _doctor_gate(_connections_report(), None)
    script = r"""
    const Cal = Application('Calendar');
    const cals = Cal.calendars();
    JSON.stringify({calendars: cals.map(c => c.name())});
    """
    info = run_jxa(script) or {}
    if "calendars" not in info:
        _die(2, "automation_denied",
             "Calendar.app did not answer — the macOS Automation grant is missing",
             "System Settings → Privacy & Security → Automation → your terminal → Calendar")
    _emit({"ok": True, "count": len(info["calendars"]), "calendars": info["calendars"]})


def cmd_calendars(args):
    script = r"""
    const Cal = Application('Calendar');
    const out = Cal.calendars().map(c => {
      let writable = null;
      try { writable = c.writable(); } catch (e) {}
      return { name: c.name(), writable: writable };
    });
    JSON.stringify(out);
    """
    cals = run_jxa(script) or []
    scope = args._scope
    if scope:
        keep = {s.strip().lower() for s in scope}
        cals = [c for c in cals if (c.get("name") or "").strip().lower() in keep]
    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps(cals, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))
        return
    banner = f"# {len(cals)} calendar(s)"
    if scope:
        banner += f" — connection {args._conn_id!r} scope"
    print(banner)
    for c in cals:
        flag = "" if c.get("writable") is not False else "  [read-only]"
        print(f"  {c['name']}{flag}")


def cmd_events(args):
    frm, to = _default_window(args.frm, args.to, days_default=7)
    wanted = _resolve_read_calendars(args)
    script = r"""
    const raw = env('CALENDARS') || '';
    const wanted = raw ? raw.split('|').map(s => s.trim()).filter(Boolean) : [];
    const cals = calendarsForNames(wanted);
    const fromDate = new Date(env('FROM'));
    const toDate = new Date(env('TO'));
    const limit = parseInt(env('LIMIT') || '0');
    const out = [];
    for (const c of cals) {
      const evs = eventsInWindow(c, fromDate, toDate);
      const calName = c.name();
      for (const e of evs) out.push(eventSummary(e, calName));
    }
    out.sort(function(a, b) {
      const as = a.startDate || '', bs = b.startDate || '';
      return as < bs ? -1 : (as > bs ? 1 : 0);
    });
    const trimmed = limit > 0 ? out.slice(0, limit) : out;
    JSON.stringify(trimmed);
    """
    events = run_jxa(script, {
        "CALENDARS": "|".join(wanted),
        "FROM": _iso(frm),
        "TO": _iso(to),
        "LIMIT": str(args.limit or 0),
    }) or []
    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps(events, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))
        return
    scope_txt = args.calendar or (", ".join(wanted) if wanted else "all calendars")
    print(f"# {scope_txt}  {_iso(frm)} .. {_iso(to)}  ({len(events)} events)")
    for e in events:
        marker = "◉" if e.get("allDay") else " "
        start = (e.get("startDate") or "")[:16].replace("T", " ")
        title = (e.get("title") or "(no title)").replace("\n", " ")
        cal = e.get("calendar") or ""
        loc = e.get("location") or ""
        print(f"{marker} [{start}] ({cal}) {title}")
        if loc:
            print(f"    @ {loc}")
        if e.get("id"):
            print(f"    id: {e['id']}")


def cmd_show(args):
    scope = args._scope
    script = r"""
    const Cal = Application('Calendar');
    const target = env('UID');
    const raw = env('CALENDARS') || '';
    const wanted = raw ? raw.split('|').map(s => s.trim()).filter(Boolean) : [];
    const cals = calendarsForNames(wanted);
    let found = null;
    let calName = null;
    for (const c of cals) {
      try {
        const hits = c.events.whose({uid: target})();
        if (hits.length > 0) { found = hits[0]; calName = c.name(); break; }
      } catch (e) {}
    }
    if (!found) die('Event not found: ' + target);
    JSON.stringify(eventFull(found, calName));
    """
    ev = run_jxa(script, {
        "UID": args.event_id,
        "CALENDARS": "|".join(scope),
    })
    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps(ev, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))
        return
    print(f"Title:    {ev.get('title')}")
    print(f"Calendar: {ev.get('calendar')}")
    print(f"Start:    {ev.get('startDate')}")
    print(f"End:      {ev.get('endDate')}")
    if ev.get("allDay"):
        print("All-day:  yes")
    if ev.get("location"):
        print(f"Location: {ev.get('location')}")
    if ev.get("url"):
        print(f"URL:      {ev.get('url')}")
    print(f"Id:       {ev.get('id')}")
    atts = ev.get("attendees") or []
    if atts:
        print("Attendees:")
        for a in atts:
            name = (a.get("name") or "").strip()
            email = a.get("email") or ""
            line = f"  - {name} <{email}>".strip() if (name or email) else "  - (unknown)"
            print(line)
    print()
    print(ev.get("notes") or "")


def cmd_search(args):
    frm, to = _default_window(args.frm, args.to, days_default=30)
    wanted = _resolve_read_calendars(args)
    script = r"""
    const raw = env('CALENDARS') || '';
    const wanted = raw ? raw.split('|').map(s => s.trim()).filter(Boolean) : [];
    const cals = calendarsForNames(wanted);
    const fromDate = new Date(env('FROM'));
    const toDate = new Date(env('TO'));
    const query = env('QUERY') || '';
    const field = env('FIELD') || 'any';
    const limit = parseInt(env('LIMIT') || '0');

    function matchClauses() {
      if (field === 'title') return [{summary: {_contains: query}}];
      if (field === 'notes') return [{description: {_contains: query}}];
      return null;   // 'any' → run two whose() calls and union
    }

    function windowClause() {
      return [
        {startDate: {'>=': fromDate}},
        {startDate: {'<': toDate}}
      ];
    }

    function runWhere(cal, extra) {
      try {
        return cal.events.whose({_and: windowClause().concat(extra)})();
      } catch (e) { return []; }
    }

    const out = [];
    const seen = {};
    for (const c of cals) {
      const calName = c.name();
      let hits = [];
      const clauses = matchClauses();
      if (clauses) {
        hits = runWhere(c, clauses);
      } else {
        // 'any' — union title-match and notes-match
        const a = runWhere(c, [{summary: {_contains: query}}]);
        const b = runWhere(c, [{description: {_contains: query}}]);
        hits = a.concat(b);
      }
      for (const e of hits) {
        const uid = (function(){try{return e.uid();}catch(x){return null;}})();
        if (uid && seen[uid]) continue;
        if (uid) seen[uid] = true;
        out.push(eventSummary(e, calName));
      }
    }
    out.sort(function(a, b) {
      const as = a.startDate || '', bs = b.startDate || '';
      return as < bs ? -1 : (as > bs ? 1 : 0);
    });
    const trimmed = limit > 0 ? out.slice(0, limit) : out;
    JSON.stringify(trimmed);
    """
    events = run_jxa(script, {
        "CALENDARS": "|".join(wanted),
        "FROM": _iso(frm),
        "TO": _iso(to),
        "QUERY": args.query,
        "FIELD": args.field,
        "LIMIT": str(args.limit or 0),
    }) or []
    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps(events, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))
        return
    scope_txt = args.calendar or (", ".join(wanted) if wanted else "all calendars")
    print(f"# search {args.query!r} in {scope_txt}  {_iso(frm)} .. {_iso(to)}  "
          f"({len(events)} hits)")
    for e in events:
        marker = "◉" if e.get("allDay") else " "
        start = (e.get("startDate") or "")[:16].replace("T", " ")
        title = (e.get("title") or "(no title)").replace("\n", " ")
        cal = e.get("calendar") or ""
        print(f"{marker} [{start}] ({cal}) {title}")
        if e.get("id"):
            print(f"    id: {e['id']}")


# Noise calendars excluded from freebusy by default. Substring, case-insensitive.
_NOISE_TOKENS = ("birthday", "birthdays", "holiday", "holidays",
                 "reminders", "siri suggestions")


def cmd_freebusy(args):
    if not args.frm or not args.to:
        sys.exit("--from and --to are required for freebusy")
    frm, to = _default_window(args.frm, args.to, days_default=7)
    scope = args._scope
    requested = [c.strip() for c in (args.calendars or "").split(",") if c.strip()]
    if requested and scope:
        keep = {s.strip().lower() for s in scope}
        bad = [c for c in requested if c.strip().lower() not in keep]
        if bad:
            _die(4, "out_of_scope",
                 f"connection {args._conn_id!r} does not include: {', '.join(bad)}",
                 "Do not lift the gate yourself — ask the user to widen the "
                 "connection's `calendars` scope in connections.json.")
        wanted = requested
    elif requested:
        wanted = requested
    else:
        wanted = list(scope)
    script = r"""
    const wantedRaw = env('CALENDARS') || '';
    const wanted = wantedRaw ? wantedRaw.split('|').map(s => s.trim()).filter(Boolean) : [];
    const includeNoise = env('INCLUDE_NOISE') === '1';
    const noiseTokens = (env('NOISE_TOKENS') || '').split('|').filter(Boolean);
    const Cal = Application('Calendar');
    const all = Cal.calendars();
    let cals;
    if (wanted.length > 0) {
      cals = calendarsForNames(wanted);
    } else {
      cals = all;
      if (!includeNoise && noiseTokens.length > 0) {
        cals = cals.filter(function(c) {
          const n = (c.name() || '').toLowerCase();
          for (const t of noiseTokens) { if (n.indexOf(t) >= 0) return false; }
          return true;
        });
      }
    }
    const fromDate = new Date(env('FROM'));
    const toDate = new Date(env('TO'));
    const busy = [];
    for (const c of cals) {
      const evs = eventsInWindow(c, fromDate, toDate);
      for (const e of evs) {
        let s = null, en = null, allDay = false;
        try { s = e.startDate(); } catch (x) {}
        try { en = e.endDate(); } catch (x) {}
        try { allDay = e.alldayEvent(); } catch (x) {}
        if (!s || !en) continue;
        // Trim to window
        if (s < fromDate) s = fromDate;
        if (en > toDate) en = toDate;
        if (en <= s) continue;
        busy.push({start: localISO(s), end: localISO(en), allDay: allDay});
      }
    }
    busy.sort(function(a, b) { return a.start < b.start ? -1 : (a.start > b.start ? 1 : 0); });
    JSON.stringify({calendars: cals.map(c => c.name()), busy: busy});
    """
    data = run_jxa(script, {
        "CALENDARS": "|".join(wanted),
        "INCLUDE_NOISE": "1" if args.include_noise else "0",
        "NOISE_TOKENS": "|".join(_NOISE_TOKENS),
        "FROM": _iso(frm),
        "TO": _iso(to),
    }) or {"busy": [], "calendars": []}

    merged = _merge_intervals(data.get("busy") or [])
    payload = {
        "from": _iso(frm),
        "to": _iso(to),
        "calendars": data.get("calendars") or [],
        "busy": merged,
    }
    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))
        return
    scope = ", ".join(payload["calendars"]) or "(no calendars)"
    print(f"# freebusy {_iso(frm)} .. {_iso(to)}")
    print(f"# calendars: {scope}")
    print(f"# {len(merged)} busy block(s)")
    for b in merged:
        s = (b.get("start") or "")[:16].replace("T", " ")
        e = (b.get("end") or "")[:16].replace("T", " ")
        print(f"  busy  {s} .. {e}")


# --- Write commands ---------------------------------------------------------

_ALARM_UNIT_SECONDS = {"s": 1, "m": 60, "h": 3600, "d": 86400}


def _parse_alarm(spec: str) -> dict:
    """Turn one --alarm SPEC into a JXA-shaped alarm descriptor:
      relative — '-15m', '-1h30m' (…) — becomes {kind:'interval', seconds: -N}
      absolute — ISO 8601 datetime — becomes {kind:'date', iso: '<ISO>'}
    Both count as `display alarm` in Calendar.app."""
    s = (spec or "").strip()
    if not s:
        _die(6, "input", "empty --alarm spec")
    if s[0] in ("-", "+"):
        sign = -1 if s[0] == "-" else 1
        body = s[1:]
        total = 0
        num = ""
        for ch in body:
            if ch.isdigit():
                num += ch
                continue
            unit = ch.lower()
            if unit not in _ALARM_UNIT_SECONDS or not num:
                _die(6, "input", f"bad alarm interval spec: {spec!r}",
                     "use forms like -15m / -1h / -1h30m / -1d")
            total += int(num) * _ALARM_UNIT_SECONDS[unit]
            num = ""
        if num:
            # trailing bare number defaults to minutes
            total += int(num) * 60
        return {"kind": "interval", "seconds": sign * total}
    try:
        datetime.fromisoformat(s)
    except ValueError:
        _die(6, "input", f"bad alarm spec: {spec!r}",
             "use a relative like -15m / -1h, or an absolute ISO datetime")
    return {"kind": "date", "iso": s}


def _write_target_calendar(args) -> str:
    """Resolve and gate the target calendar of a write verb."""
    name = getattr(args, "calendar", None)
    if not name:
        _die(6, "input", "--calendar is required for write verbs")
    _enforce_write(args._conn_id, args._scope, args._allow_write, args.cmd, name)
    return name


CREATE_JXA = r"""
const Cal = Application('Calendar');
const cals = calendarsForNames([env('CALENDAR')]);
if (cals.length === 0) die('No calendar matches: ' + env('CALENDAR'));
const cal = cals[0];
const payload = JSON.parse(env('PAYLOAD'));
const props = {
  summary: payload.title,
  startDate: new Date(payload.startDate),
  endDate: new Date(payload.endDate)
};
if (payload.allDay) props.alldayEvent = true;
if (payload.location) props.location = payload.location;
if (payload.notes) props.description = payload.notes;
if (payload.url) props.url = payload.url;
const ev = Cal.Event(props);
cal.events.push(ev);
for (const email of (payload.invitees || [])) {
  try {
    const att = Cal.Attendee({email: email});
    ev.attendees.push(att);
  } catch (e) {}
}
for (const alarm of (payload.alarms || [])) {
  try {
    let a;
    if (alarm.kind === 'interval') {
      a = Cal.DisplayAlarm({triggerInterval: alarm.seconds});
    } else {
      a = Cal.DisplayAlarm({triggerDate: new Date(alarm.iso)});
    }
    ev.displayAlarms.push(a);
  } catch (e) {}
}
JSON.stringify({uid: ev.uid(), calendar: cal.name()});
"""


UPDATE_JXA = r"""
const Cal = Application('Calendar');
const target = env('UID');
const raw = env('CALENDARS') || '';
const wanted = raw ? raw.split('|').map(s => s.trim()).filter(Boolean) : [];
const cals = calendarsForNames(wanted);
let found = null;
let calName = null;
for (const c of cals) {
  try {
    const hits = c.events.whose({uid: target})();
    if (hits.length > 0) { found = hits[0]; calName = c.name(); break; }
  } catch (e) {}
}
if (!found) die('Event not found in scope: ' + target);
const payload = JSON.parse(env('PAYLOAD'));
if (payload.title !== undefined) found.summary = payload.title;
if (payload.startDate !== undefined) found.startDate = new Date(payload.startDate);
if (payload.endDate !== undefined) found.endDate = new Date(payload.endDate);
if (payload.allDay !== undefined) found.alldayEvent = payload.allDay;
if (payload.location !== undefined) found.location = payload.location;
if (payload.notes !== undefined) found.description = payload.notes;
if (payload.url !== undefined) found.url = payload.url;
for (const email of (payload.addInvitees || [])) {
  try {
    const att = Cal.Attendee({email: email});
    found.attendees.push(att);
  } catch (e) {}
}
if (payload.alarms) {
  try {
    const existing = found.displayAlarms();
    for (let i = existing.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
      try { existing[i].delete(); } catch (e) {}
    }
  } catch (e) {}
  for (const alarm of payload.alarms) {
    try {
      let a;
      if (alarm.kind === 'interval') {
        a = Cal.DisplayAlarm({triggerInterval: alarm.seconds});
      } else {
        a = Cal.DisplayAlarm({triggerDate: new Date(alarm.iso)});
      }
      found.displayAlarms.push(a);
    } catch (e) {}
  }
}
JSON.stringify({uid: found.uid(), calendar: calName});
"""


DELETE_JXA = r"""
const Cal = Application('Calendar');
const target = env('UID');
const raw = env('CALENDARS') || '';
const wanted = raw ? raw.split('|').map(s => s.trim()).filter(Boolean) : [];
const cals = calendarsForNames(wanted);
let found = null;
let calName = null;
for (const c of cals) {
  try {
    const hits = c.events.whose({uid: target})();
    if (hits.length > 0) { found = hits[0]; calName = c.name(); break; }
  } catch (e) {}
}
if (!found) die('Event not found in scope: ' + target);
Cal.delete(found);
JSON.stringify({deleted: target, calendar: calName});
"""


def cmd_create(args):
    frm = _parse_iso(args.frm, _local_now())
    to = _parse_iso(args.to, frm + timedelta(hours=1))
    if to <= frm and not args.all_day:
        sys.exit("--to must be after --from")
    calendar = _write_target_calendar(args)
    payload = {
        "title": args.title,
        "startDate": _iso(frm),
        "endDate": _iso(to),
        "allDay": bool(args.all_day),
        "location": args.location,
        "notes": args.notes,
        "url": args.url,
        "invitees": args.invitee or [],
        "alarms": [_parse_alarm(a) for a in (args.alarm or [])],
    }
    result = run_jxa(CREATE_JXA, {
        "CALENDAR": calendar,
        "PAYLOAD": json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False),
    }) or {}
    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps(result, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))
        return
    uid = (result or {}).get("uid")
    cal_out = (result or {}).get("calendar")
    if not uid:
        sys.exit("event created but no uid returned")
    print(f"created  ({cal_out}) {args.title}")
    print(f"    id: {uid}")


def cmd_update(args):
    payload: dict = {}
    if args.title is not None:
        payload["title"] = args.title
    if args.frm is not None:
        payload["startDate"] = _iso(_parse_iso(args.frm, _local_now()))
    if args.to is not None:
        payload["endDate"] = _iso(_parse_iso(args.to, _local_now()))
    if args.all_day:
        payload["allDay"] = True
    if args.no_all_day:
        payload["allDay"] = False
    if args.location is not None:
        payload["location"] = args.location
    if args.notes is not None:
        payload["notes"] = args.notes
    if args.url is not None:
        payload["url"] = args.url
    if args.add_invitee:
        payload["addInvitees"] = args.add_invitee
    if args.alarm:
        payload["alarms"] = [_parse_alarm(a) for a in args.alarm]
    if not payload:
        sys.exit("update: at least one field flag is required")

    scope = args._scope
    # For update we don't know the calendar up front — look it up first, then
    # gate. Cheapest is to resolve within the connection scope in JXA.
    lookup_script = r"""
    (function() {
      const Cal = Application('Calendar');
      const target = env('UID');
      const raw = env('CALENDARS') || '';
      const wanted = raw ? raw.split('|').map(s => s.trim()).filter(Boolean) : [];
      const cals = calendarsForNames(wanted);
      for (const c of cals) {
        try {
          const hits = c.events.whose({uid: target})();
          if (hits.length > 0) return JSON.stringify({calendar: c.name()});
        } catch (e) {}
      }
      die('Event not found in scope: ' + target);
    })();
    """
    found = run_jxa(lookup_script, {
        "UID": args.event_id,
        "CALENDARS": "|".join(scope),
    })
    cal_of = (found or {}).get("calendar") if isinstance(found, dict) else None
    if not cal_of:
        sys.exit(f"event not found in scope: {args.event_id}")
    _enforce_write(args._conn_id, scope, args._allow_write, "update", cal_of)

    result = run_jxa(UPDATE_JXA, {
        "UID": args.event_id,
        "CALENDARS": "|".join(scope),
        "PAYLOAD": json.dumps(payload, ensure_ascii=False),
    }) or {}
    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps(result, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))
        return
    print(f"updated  ({result.get('calendar')}) id: {result.get('uid')}")


def cmd_delete(args):
    scope = args._scope
    lookup_script = r"""
    (function() {
      const Cal = Application('Calendar');
      const target = env('UID');
      const raw = env('CALENDARS') || '';
      const wanted = raw ? raw.split('|').map(s => s.trim()).filter(Boolean) : [];
      const cals = calendarsForNames(wanted);
      for (const c of cals) {
        try {
          const hits = c.events.whose({uid: target})();
          if (hits.length > 0) return JSON.stringify({calendar: c.name()});
        } catch (e) {}
      }
      die('Event not found in scope: ' + target);
    })();
    """
    found = run_jxa(lookup_script, {
        "UID": args.event_id,
        "CALENDARS": "|".join(scope),
    })
    cal_of = (found or {}).get("calendar") if isinstance(found, dict) else None
    if not cal_of:
        sys.exit(f"event not found in scope: {args.event_id}")
    _enforce_write(args._conn_id, scope, args._allow_write, "delete", cal_of)

    result = run_jxa(DELETE_JXA, {
        "UID": args.event_id,
        "CALENDARS": "|".join(scope),
    }) or {}
    if args.json:
        print(json.dumps(result, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2))
        return
    print(f"deleted  ({result.get('calendar')}) id: {result.get('deleted')}")


def _merge_intervals(items: list[dict]) -> list[dict]:
    """Merge overlapping/touching [start, end] intervals. Parses ISO strings
    with offsets; comparison is done as timezone-aware datetimes so the merge is
    correct across DST boundaries."""
    parsed: list[tuple[datetime, datetime]] = []
    for it in items:
        s, e = it.get("start"), it.get("end")
        if not s or not e:
            continue
        try:
            parsed.append((datetime.fromisoformat(s), datetime.fromisoformat(e)))
        except ValueError:
            continue
    if not parsed:
        return []
    parsed.sort(key=lambda p: p[0])
    out: list[tuple[datetime, datetime]] = []
    cs, ce = parsed[0]
    for s, e in parsed[1:]:
        if s <= ce:
            if e > ce:
                ce = e
        else:
            out.append((cs, ce))
            cs, ce = s, e
    out.append((cs, ce))
    return [{"start": _iso(s), "end": _iso(e)} for s, e in out]


def main():
    _gate()                      # every verb passes the project gate first
    _contract(sys.argv[1:])      # contract verbs; domain verbs fall through
    cleaned, wanted_conn = _extract_connection(sys.argv[1:])

    p = argparse.ArgumentParser(
        prog="ical",
        description="Personal Calendar.app CLI (JXA; read + write, "
                    "connection-gated).",
    )
    sub = p.add_subparsers(dest="cmd", required=True)

    sub.add_parser("help", help="Print the full usage contract.")
    sub.add_parser("doctor", help="Prove the macOS Automation grant.")

    pc = sub.add_parser("calendars", help="List Calendar.app calendars.")
    pc.add_argument("--json", action="store_true")

    pe = sub.add_parser("events", help="List events in a date window.")
    pe.add_argument("--calendar", help="Restrict to one calendar (case-insensitive)")
    pe.add_argument("--from", dest="frm", help="ISO datetime; window start (default: today)")
    pe.add_argument("--to", help="ISO datetime; window end (default: today+7d)")
    pe.add_argument("--limit", type=int, default=0, help="Cap results (0 = no cap)")
    pe.add_argument("--json", action="store_true")

    psh = sub.add_parser("show", help="Show one event by uid.")
    psh.add_argument("event_id")
    psh.add_argument("--json", action="store_true")

    ps = sub.add_parser("search", help="Search events.")
    ps.add_argument("query")
    ps.add_argument("--calendar", help="Restrict to one calendar (case-insensitive)")
    ps.add_argument("--from", dest="frm", help="ISO datetime; window start (default: today)")
    ps.add_argument("--to", help="ISO datetime; window end (default: today+30d)")
    ps.add_argument("--field", choices=["title", "notes", "any"], default="any")
    ps.add_argument("--limit", type=int, default=0)
    ps.add_argument("--json", action="store_true")

    pf = sub.add_parser("freebusy", help="Merged busy blocks across a window.")
    pf.add_argument("--from", dest="frm", required=True,
                    help="ISO datetime; window start")
    pf.add_argument("--to", required=True, help="ISO datetime; window end")
    pf.add_argument("--calendars",
                    help="Comma-separated calendar names; default: every "
                         "calendar minus obvious noise (Birthdays/Holidays/"
                         "Reminders/Siri Suggestions)")
    pf.add_argument("--include-noise", action="store_true",
                    help="Include Birthdays/Holidays/Reminders/Siri Suggestions "
                         "in the default-all set")
    pf.add_argument("--json", action="store_true")

    pcr = sub.add_parser("create", help="Create an event (write-gated).")
    pcr.add_argument("--calendar", required=True,
                     help="Target calendar name (must be in the connection scope)")
    pcr.add_argument("--title", required=True)
    pcr.add_argument("--from", dest="frm", required=True,
                     help="ISO datetime; event start")
    pcr.add_argument("--to", required=True, help="ISO datetime; event end")
    pcr.add_argument("--all-day", action="store_true", dest="all_day")
    pcr.add_argument("--location")
    pcr.add_argument("--notes", help="Description / notes")
    pcr.add_argument("--url", help="URL (use for a video-call link)")
    pcr.add_argument("--invitee", action="append", metavar="EMAIL",
                     help="Attendee email (repeatable)")
    pcr.add_argument("--alarm", action="append", metavar="SPEC",
                     help="Alarm: relative (-15m, -1h, -1d) or absolute ISO "
                          "(repeatable)")
    pcr.add_argument("--json", action="store_true")

    pup = sub.add_parser("update", help="Update an event by uid (write-gated).")
    pup.add_argument("event_id")
    pup.add_argument("--title")
    pup.add_argument("--from", dest="frm")
    pup.add_argument("--to")
    pup.add_argument("--all-day", action="store_true", dest="all_day")
    pup.add_argument("--no-all-day", action="store_true", dest="no_all_day")
    pup.add_argument("--location")
    pup.add_argument("--notes")
    pup.add_argument("--url")
    pup.add_argument("--add-invitee", action="append", metavar="EMAIL",
                     dest="add_invitee",
                     help="Add attendee email (repeatable)")
    pup.add_argument("--alarm", action="append", metavar="SPEC",
                     help="Replace alarm set; relative or absolute ISO "
                          "(repeatable)")
    pup.add_argument("--json", action="store_true")

    pdel = sub.add_parser("delete", help="Delete an event by uid (write-gated).")
    pdel.add_argument("event_id")
    pdel.add_argument("--json", action="store_true")

    args = p.parse_args(cleaned)

    if args.cmd == "help":
        sys.stdout.write((__doc__ or "").lstrip("\n"))
        return
    if args.cmd == "doctor":
        cmd_doctor()
        return

    # Resolve the active connection once; attach to args for every dispatch.
    args._conn_id, args._scope, args._allow_write = _active_conn(wanted_conn)

    dispatch = {
        "calendars": cmd_calendars,
        "events": cmd_events,
        "show": cmd_show,
        "search": cmd_search,
        "freebusy": cmd_freebusy,
        "create": cmd_create,
        "update": cmd_update,
        "delete": cmd_delete,
    }
    dispatch[args.cmd](args)


if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()
